description: A Roman period rectangular enclosure of 1m-wide chalk walls discovered during evaluation by Canterbury Archaeological Trust. Interpreted as a possible shrine or monumental enclosure.
bibliography: Mackinder. “Romano-British Site at Swanscombe, Kent,” 2010. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030407.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Swan Valley Community School (Kent).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
Pratt. “Swanscombe Thameside Community School: Archaeological Evaluation,” 1997. https://doi.org/10.5284/1027371.
